Speaker Notes

The balance should be approximately:

20% space exploration
25% infrastructure (GPS, Moonlight, communications)
25% networking concepts
20% RADIANT
10% call to action

For EMF, the key is that the audience leaves talking about "building infrastructure beyond Earth", not about BPv7, AX.25, or protocol stacks. Those details can come out during questions or over a beer afterwards. The talk should make RADIANT feel like a tangible amateur contribution to the broader challenge of building a connected cislunar future.